  "prompt": "What business model does olx use?",
  "response": "OLX primarily operates as a peer-to-peer (P2P) online classifieds platform where users can buy and sell various goods and services. Their key business model characteristics include:\n\n1. Digital Marketplace Model\n- Free listing for individual sellers\n- Platform connecting buyers and sellers\n- Revenue generated through advertising and premium listings\n\n2. Revenue Streams\n- Sponsored listings\n- Featured ad placements\n- Advertising\n- Potential commission on certain transactions\n- Premium seller services\n\n3. Platform Structure\n- Website and mobile app\n- User-generated content\n- No direct inventory ownership\n- Facilitates transactions between users\n\n4. Geographic Expansion\n- Operates in multiple countries\n- Adapts to local market needs\n- Localized platforms in different regions\n\n5. Monetization Strategies\n- Freemium model (basic services free, premium features paid)\n- Targeted advertising\n- Enhanced visibility options for sellers\n\n6. Technology Focus\n- User-friendly interface\n- Mobile-first approach\n- Advanced search and filtering capabilities\n\nThe business model centers on creating a convenient, accessible platform for local buying and selling, generating revenue through indirect monetization methods while providing value to users.",
